<docs>
   <doc for="MTx">
 <summary>
    <para>
        Provides functionality necessary to create and reference objects
        in MTS.
    </para>
 </summary>
   </doc>
   <doc for="MTx.CreateObject">
 <summary>
    <para>
       Create an object given a progID.
    </para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
    <para>
       In an MTS environment, it is necessary to create ServicedComponents
       via the CreateObject helper if you expect to inherit services
       from your current context.
    </para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
   <doc for="MTx.CreateObject1">
 <summary>
    <para>
       Create an object given a class ID.
    </para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
    <para>
       In an MTS environment, it is necessary to create ServicedComponents
       via the CreateObject helper if you expect to inherit services
       from your current context.
    </para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
   <doc for="MTx.SafeRef">
 <summary>
    <para>
        Create an object reference that is safe to pass back
        to a client.
    </para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
    <para>
        When passing a reference to an object local to your
        context (such as this) out via a return value or an out parameter,
        it is necessary to first create an MTS proxy around that object via
        SafeRef.
    </para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
</docs>

